        </p>
        <p>
          Section 3.4 of this Agreement does not apply to the extent that reverse
          engineering or debugging is necessary to exercise those rights, nor to the
          extent that applicable law confers a right that may not be excluded by
          contract.
        </p>

        <h3>6. Source code</h3>
        <p>
          The Software is proprietary. It is not open-source software. No source code
          for the Software itself is made available, and nothing in this Agreement
          grants you any right to it.
        </p>

        <h3>7. Privacy</h3>
        <p>
          The Software converts images entirely on the local device. It does not
          upload your images, does not transmit their contents or filenames to us or
          to any third party, does not require an account, and functions without a
          network connection.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Software calls Microsoft Store services to check for application
          updates and, where you choose to leave a rating, to submit that rating.
          Those calls are handled by Microsoft under its own privacy terms.
        </p>

        <h3>8. No warranty</h3>
        <p class="legal-caps">
          THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
          IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY,
          FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not warrant that the Software will be uninterrupted or error-free,
          that it will convert any given file correctly, or that it will remain
          available.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Your attention is drawn in particular to the following.</strong> The
          Software offers options to delete or move original files after conversion.
          Those operations are irreversible. You are solely responsible for
          maintaining backups of any file you process. We recommend that you verify
          conversion results before enabling either option on data you cannot afford
